a doctor, but we manage.

245
00:17:12,758 --> 00:17:16,345
- One-twelves!
- Excuse me, Mr. Blume. Nice talking to you.

246
00:17:18,639 --> 00:17:20,349
You're on the team?

247
00:17:21,225 --> 00:17:22,351
I'm an alternate.

248
00:17:23,561 --> 00:17:26,397
How you doin'?
Good to see you again.

249
00:17:35,114 --> 00:17:38,325
Whoa. Neat.

250
00:18:57,738 --> 00:18:59,657
<i>Miss Cross?</i>

251
00:18:59,782 --> 00:19:02,910
I thought I'd just let you know
as per our conversation, the other day...

252
00:19:02,993 --> 00:19:05,663
- Latin?
- Right. The Romance languages.

253
00:19:05,704 --> 00:19:08,499
- Well, I gave a little speech.
- I heard about this.

254
00:19:08,582 --> 00:19:10,000
Oh, you did?

255
00:19:10,126 --> 00:19:13,838
I understand you made
a very convincing argument.

256
00:19:14,672 --> 00:19:19,468
I just thought you'd be pleased to hear
they're gonna continue the Latin program.

257
00:19:19,635 --> 00:19:21,512
I'm very impressed.

258
00:19:21,679 --> 00:19:24,265
Well, thank you very much.

259
00:19:24,849 --> 00:19:26,934
Hey, you need an assistant?

260
00:19:27,184 --> 00:19:30,688
- Do we get to have
an assistant around here?
- No, I doubt it.

261
00:19:30,729 --> 00:19:33,190
I'm on scholarship, though...
academic scholarship...

262
00:19:33,274 --> 00:19:35,860
so I get to do odd jobs and...

263
00:19:35,943 --> 00:19:38,529
Say, how did you decide
to teach at Rushmore?

264
00:19:38,612 --> 00:19:40,531
My husband went here.

265
00:19:42,950 --> 00:19:47,455
I, uh... I didn't know
you were married.

266
00:19:47,621 --> 00:19:49,540
Well, he's dead now.

267
00:19:49,623 --> 00:19:51,542
So I'm not, actually.

268
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:53,878
When did he die?

269
00:19:54,044 --> 00:19:55,713
Last year.

270
00:19:57,298 --> 00:19:59,216
My mother's dead.

271
00:20:00,301 --> 00:20:02,344
I'm sorry to hear that.

272
00:20:02,511 --> 00:20:05,139
She died when I was seven.

273
00:20:05,306 --> 00:20:08,392
I guess we both have
dead people in our families.

274
00:20:12,980 --> 00:20:15,399
What's going on in here?

275
00:20:17,485 --> 00:20:19,779
These were just born.

276
00:20:21,989 --> 00:20:25,034
I don't want alloys. I want steel.

277
00:20:26,076 --> 00:20:29,413
I don't give a rat's ass what he says.

278
00:20:31,499 --> 00:20:33,542
Steel, Harry.

279
00:20:34,251 --> 00:20:37,421
- So you've changed your mind,
and you want the job?
- No.

280
00:20:37,505 --> 00:20:39,757
But I've got an idea,
and I need some money.

281
00:20:40,466 --> 00:20:42,426
What Rushmore
needs is an aquarium...

282
00:20:42,510 --> 00:20:45,095
a first-class aquarium...
where the scientists can lecture...

283
00:20:45,179 --> 00:20:48,432
and the students can observe
the marine life in its natural habitat.

284
00:20:48,557 --> 00:20:51,060
- I don't know.
What do you think, Ernie?
- An aquarium?

285
00:20:51,143 --> 00:20:55,106
- What kind of fish?
- Barracudas, stingrays,
electric eel, trout,

286
00:20:55,189 --> 00:20:58,109
hammerheads, piranhas,
giant squid, octopi...

287
00:20:58,192 --> 00:21:02,196
- Piranhas? Really?
- Yes, I'm talking
to a guy in South America.

288
00:21:02,279 --> 00:21:05,991
- What'd Guggenheim say?
- Nothing. I felt I should go to you first.

289
00:21:06,117 --> 00:21:07,993
Why?

290
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:11,747
Because at this moment, I feel the
best strategy is to keep it low profile.

291
00:21:11,789 --> 00:21:14,750
The more preparation work I can do,
the stronger our case will be...

292
00:21:14,792 --> 00:21:17,795
- when we take it to the administration.
- How much money do you want?

293
00:21:18,295 --> 00:21:22,091
Thirty-five thousand dollars,
for the initial plans.

294
00:21:31,809 --> 00:21:33,978
I'll give you 2,500.

295
00:21:34,145 --> 00:21:35,521
Okay.

296
00:22:23,736 --> 00:22:25,696
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

297
00:23:03,609 --> 00:23:05,903
- Max.
- Mm-hmm?

298
00:23:06,070 --> 00:23:09,448
- Can I ask you something?
- Sure.

299
00:23:10,491 --> 00:23:14,286
Has it ever crossed your mind
that you're far too young for me?

300
00:23:19,375 --> 00:23:23,003
It crossed my mind that you might
consider that a possibility. Yeah.

301
00:23:23,087 --> 00:23:25,464
Quite apart from the fact
that you're a student...

302
00:23:25,589 --> 00:23:28,509
I'm not trying to pressure you
into anything, Miss Cross.

303
00:23:28,592 --> 00:23:32,471
- I'm surprised you
brought it up so bluntly.
- I just want to make sure...

304
00:23:35,266 --> 00:23:38,060
- We've become friends, haven't we?
- Yes.

305
00:23:38,185 --> 00:23:39,854
Good.

306
00:23:40,354 --> 00:23:42,648
And, um...

307
00:23:42,773 --> 00:23:46,277
the... the truth is, neither
one of us has the slightest idea...

308
00:23:46,360 --> 00:23:48,195
where this relationship is going.

309
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:51,907
- We can't predict the future.
- We don't have a relationship, Max.

310
00:23:51,991 --> 00:23:54,827
- But we're friends.
- Yes, and that's all we're going to be.

311
00:23:54,952 --> 00:23:57,496
That's all I meant by "relationship".

312
00:23:57,621 --> 00:23:59,373
You want me to grab a dictionary?

313
00:23:59,498 --> 00:24:03,210
No, I just want to make sure
that we understand each other.

314
00:24:03,335 --> 00:24:05,296
I understand.

315
00:24:05,463 --> 00:24:08,466
You're not attracted to me.

316
00:24:08,632 --> 00:24:10,551
<i>C'est la vie.</i>

317
00:24:11,302 --> 00:24:13,762
Max, you're 15 years old.

318
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:17,057
Attraction doesn't enter into it.

319
00:24:17,183 --> 00:24:19,101
If you say so.

320
00:24:19,226 --> 00:24:21,437
Look, all I'm getting at is that...

321
00:24:24,398 --> 00:24:26,942
that I've never met anyone like you.

322
00:24:28,736 --> 00:24:31,322
So you can take that
for whatever it's worth.

323
00:24:33,741 --> 00:24:38,162
I think I can safely say
I've never met anyone like you either.

324
00:24:42,041 --> 00:24:43,876
You haven't, have you?

325
00:24:46,712 --> 00:24:48,881
Want to shake hands?

326
00:24:50,007 --> 00:24:52,843
I'm glad we had this conversation.

327
00:24:53,010 --> 00:24:54,345
So am I.

328
00:24:56,055 --> 00:24:58,182
I can't wear a wire.
They're feeling me up every day.

329
00:24:58,307 --> 00:25:01,143
Oh, come on, Frank.
You'll have complete protection.

330
00:25:01,268 --> 00:25:03,104
Yeah, I've heard that one before.

331
00:25:03,187 --> 00:25:05,272
- I gotta put a dime in the meter.
- Sit down, Frank.

332
00:25:05,356 --> 00:25:08,692
Joe, go put a dime in the meter
for Officer Serpico.

333
00:25:08,859 --> 00:25:12,154
- Look, Serpico, if you agree
to testify in open court...
- No!

334
00:25:12,279 --> 00:25:15,491
- No, what?
- No, I'm not gonna testify.

335
00:25:15,616 --> 00:25:17,034
Go, go, go.

336
00:25:17,535 --> 00:25:20,955
I'll expect your gun
and your badge on my desk...

337
00:25:21,872 --> 00:25:23,999
- Promise me one thing, O'Reilly.
- Name it.

338
00:25:24,041 --> 00:25:26,752
That you're gonna follow this thing
all the way to the end...

339
00:25:26,877 --> 00:25:29,130
of the line... where I got to be.

340
00:25:29,255 --> 00:25:30,923
So help me God.

341
00:25:31,090 --> 00:25:33,050
<i>- Someone coming out of the building.</i>
- I've got something!

342
00:25:33,134 --> 00:25:36,178
<i>- Wait. This could be it.</i>
- There's action across the street.

343
00:25:36,303 --> 00:25:38,597
<i>- Yeah, it's him.</i>
- It's Snowman.

344
00:25:40,850 --> 00:25:43,144
- He's getting on the "L" train!
- Take him!

345
00:25:45,479 --> 00:25:47,648
- What happened to the cannoli line?
- Max...

346
00:25:47,731 --> 00:25:50,943
You're supposed to say,
"Forget about it, Sanchez.
The old man likes his cannolis".

347
00:25:51,026 --> 00:25:53,654
Look, I made a mistake, all right?
It didn't make any difference anyway.

348
00:25:53,779 --> 00:25:56,323
Hey, I'm letting it go,
but don't say it doesn't matter.

349
00:25:56,407 --> 00:25:58,993
- Every line matters.
- Get off my back!

350
00:25:59,076 --> 00:26:01,036
Don't fuck with my play!

351
00:26:01,704 --> 00:26:03,664
- You fucking cocksucker...
- Hey, break it up. Break it up.

352
00:26:03,831 --> 00:26:05,541
I'm gonna kill you.

353
00:26:12,548 --> 00:26:15,092
Max. Max.

354
00:26:40,034 --> 00:26:42,745
- I thought the acting
tonight was excellent.
- Thanks.

355
00:26:42,870 --> 00:26:45,456
Well, it was better in rehearsals.

356
00:26:45,623 --> 00:26:48,250
I'll catch up with you later, Dad.
I got a dinner to go to.

357
00:26:48,375 --> 00:26:51,670
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah. Cast and crew only.

358
00:26:51,754 --> 00:26:54,799
- Oh. You need some money?
- No, Dad.

359
00:26:57,927 --> 00:27:00,721
- Well, how was the slap?
- It was good.

360
00:27:00,846 --> 00:27:04,058
- There he is. Max, that was great.
- I'm so glad you could come.

361
00:27:04,183 --> 00:27:07,144
I want you to meet a friend of mine.
Peter Flynn, Max Fischer.

362
00:27:07,186 --> 00:27:09,605
- Hi.
- Who's this guy?

363
00:27:11,357 --> 00:27:16,237
- Peter.
- I really liked your play.
It was really cool.

364
00:27:16,403 --> 00:27:19,782
- Yeah.
- What happened to your nose?

365
00:27:20,699 --> 00:27:23,285
- I got punched in the face.
- Oh, boy.

366
00:27:23,369 --> 00:27:26,705
- What's your excuse?
- Hey, author.

367
00:27:26,831 --> 00:27:28,332
- How you doing?
- Nice job.

368
00:27:28,457 --> 00:27:30,960
- Thank you.
- Gonna get to meet your dad tonight?

369
00:27:31,043 --> 00:27:33,003
Oh, no. The old man's on call.

370
00:27:33,045 --> 00:27:35,005
Mr. Blume, I'd like you
to meet Miss Cross...

371
00:27:35,047 --> 00:27:38,008
and I didn't catch
this young gentleman's name.

372
00:27:39,343 --> 00:27:42,221
I like your nurse's uniform, guy.

373
00:27:42,346 --> 00:27:44,807
These are O.R. scrubs.

374
00:27:45,015 --> 00:27:47,101
"O.R." they?

375
00:27:49,019 --> 00:27:51,772
Well, they're totally
inappropriate for the occasion.

376
00:27:51,897 --> 00:27:54,150
Well, I didn't know
we were going to dinner.

377
00:27:54,316 --> 00:27:56,569
That's because you weren't invited.

378
00:27:56,735 --> 00:28:01,157
- Take it easy, Max.
- You were the one that ordered
him a whiskey and soda.

379
00:28:01,323 --> 00:28:03,033
So what's wrong with that?

380
00:28:03,159 --> 00:28:07,413
I can write a hit play. Why can't I have
a little drink to unwind myself?

381
00:28:09,290 --> 00:28:11,917
So, tell me, curly,
how do you know Miss Cross?

382
00:28:12,042 --> 00:28:14,086
- We went to Harvard together.
- Oh, that's great.

383
00:28:14,211 --> 00:28:16,130
I wrote a hit play
and directed it.

384
00:28:16,213 --> 00:28:18,549
So I'm not sweating it either.

385
00:28:18,716 --> 00:28:20,134
Can we get a check, please?

386
00:28:20,217 --> 00:28:22,428
- What do you think you're doing?
- Getting the check.

387
00:28:22,553 --> 00:28:24,472
No, you're not. Excuse me.

388
00:28:24,638 --> 00:28:26,599
I just want to thank you
for accommodating us.

389
00:28:26,724 --> 00:28:28,768
You see, we only thought
we were going to be three,

390
00:28:28,893 --> 00:28:32,271
but, uh, someone invited
himself along, so I apologize.

391
00:28:32,396 --> 00:28:35,775
- Quite all right, sir. Very well.
- Okay.

392
00:28:35,941 --> 00:28:37,610
You're being rude, Max.

393
00:28:37,777 --> 00:28:39,153
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

394
00:28:39,278 --> 00:28:42,656
No, I'm not. I'm just trying to figure out
why you brought this gentleman to my play...

395
00:28:42,782 --> 00:28:45,701
and my dinner,
which was invitation only.

396
00:28:46,285 --> 00:28:49,205
- Would you like me
to pass you the creamer, Doc?
- Yes, please.

397
00:28:50,289 --> 00:28:53,292
- What is wrong with you?
- What is wrong with you?

398
00:28:53,417 --> 00:28:57,254
You hurt my feelings!
This night was important to me!

399
00:28:57,421 --> 00:28:59,381
How did I hurt your feelings?

400
00:28:59,465 --> 00:29:03,844
Oh, my God!
I wrote a hit play!

401
00:29:08,015 --> 00:29:10,434
And I'm in love with you.

402
00:29:19,110 --> 00:29:21,112
Put that a little bit there.

403
00:29:40,506 --> 00:29:44,218
- Hi.
- Were you hiding over there?

404
00:29:44,385 --> 00:29:47,471
Uh, I didn't want
to disrupt class.

405
00:29:49,014 --> 00:29:50,975
What's that you're painting?

406
00:29:51,016 --> 00:29:54,270
That's a... a jellyfish.

407
00:29:54,728 --> 00:29:57,231
What can I do for you, Mr. Blume?

408
00:29:57,398 --> 00:29:59,442
Max wants to talk to you.

409
00:29:59,525 --> 00:30:03,279
- What for?
- To apologize, I think.

410
00:30:04,029 --> 00:30:05,781
Should we talk over here?

411
00:30:08,075 --> 00:30:09,326
He sent you?

412
00:30:09,368 --> 00:30:10,995
Yeah.

413
00:30:11,537 --> 00:30:13,914
Are you his messenger?

414
00:30:14,665 --> 00:30:17,251
No, I'm his friend.

415
00:30:17,501 --> 00:30:21,964
You were right.
I should not have allowed him to drink.

416
00:30:23,716 --> 00:30:27,303
I don't think
I should see Max anymore.

417
00:30:27,470 --> 00:30:30,014
Well, he's not gonna like
the sound of that.

418
00:30:30,181 --> 00:30:32,808
No. No, I know, but...

419
00:30:32,975 --> 00:30:35,811
I think I let him
get too attached.

420
00:30:36,729 --> 00:30:38,147
What do you think?

421
00:30:39,523 --> 00:30:41,484
Well, I think
you did your best.

422
00:30:45,488 --> 00:30:47,656
Tell him I'm sorry.

423
00:30:53,078 --> 00:30:55,039
Okay.

424
00:30:57,458 --> 00:30:59,794
What is your first name?

425
00:31:00,961 --> 00:31:04,590
Rosemary. What's yours?

426
00:31:04,757 --> 00:31:06,133
Herman.

427
00:31:10,554 --> 00:31:12,431
He wrote you a letter.

428
00:31:12,598 --> 00:31:14,308
<i>Dear Miss Cross,</i>

429
00:31:14,391 --> 00:31:16,811
<i>I would like to take this opportunity</i>
<i>to formally apologize...</i>

430
00:31:16,894 --> 00:31:19,438
<i>for the events</i>
<i>of the night of the 23rd.</i>

431
00:31:19,563 --> 00:31:22,149
<i>I'm not accustomed</i>
<i>to drinking alcohol.</i>

432
00:31:22,233 --> 00:31:26,445
<i>Please do me the service</i>
<i>of coming to the unveiling of</i>
<i>a new venture I've undertaken.</i>

433
00:31:26,529 --> 00:31:29,406
<i>I hope you will attend,</i>
<i>if possible.</i>

434
00:31:29,573 --> 00:31:32,868
<i>I remain your friend, Max Fischer.</i>

435
00:31:40,167 --> 00:31:42,336
Cut the music and no more pictures.

436
00:31:42,419 --> 00:31:44,630
- What time is it, Alan?
- 1:15.

437
00:31:44,755 --> 00:31:47,758
Excuse me, gentlemen.
Hey, lay off the chips, Buchan.

438
00:31:48,509 --> 00:31:49,343
Did you see her?

439
00:31:49,426 --> 00:31:51,679
- She's not here.
- Well, go check her classroom.

440
00:31:51,762 --> 00:31:54,181
- Shall I go ahead
and take care of this tree?
- Let's wait a few minutes.

441
00:31:54,265 --> 00:31:57,143
- What's going on here, Maxie?
- Oh, hey, Coach Beck. Good to see you.

442
00:31:57,268 --> 00:31:58,853
This is where we're
putting in the new aquarium.

443
00:31:58,936 --> 00:32:00,855
I'm in charge of the committee,
if you can believe it.

444
00:32:00,938 --> 00:32:03,607
This is my baseball diamond.

445
00:32:03,816 --> 00:32:07,695
Yeah, I know, and I believe
it's being relocated a few feet over.

446
00:32:07,778 --> 00:32:10,489
Is it true the aquarium
will have piranhas?

447
00:32:10,656 --> 00:32:14,368
- Where did you hear that?
- My source indicated
that it was a possibility.

448
00:32:14,577 --> 00:32:16,954
Yes, it's true, but piranhas
are a very tricky species.

449
00:32:17,037 --> 00:32:19,790
- Max?
- Excuse me, George.

450
00:32:19,874 --> 00:32:21,792
- Bad news.
- What's the story?

451
00:32:21,876 --> 00:32:24,128
- She had a substitute teacher today.
- Why?

452
00:32:24,211 --> 00:32:27,631
- I guess she got sick.
- You know she's not sick.
Give me the phone.

453
00:32:31,719 --> 00:32:33,971
Janet, Max Fischer.
Is Mr. Blume there?

454
00:32:35,764 --> 00:32:37,391
Well, where is he?

455
00:32:38,017 --> 00:32:39,935
Goddamn it.
He's supposed to be here.

456
00:32:40,770 --> 00:32:42,605
I don't give a shit
about the barracudas,

457
00:32:42,646 --> 00:32:45,149
but, fuck it, I'm building it anyway.

458
00:32:47,026 --> 00:32:48,152
Max!

459
00:32:48,319 --> 00:32:50,154
Where are those damn
chain saws coming from?

460
00:32:50,237 --> 00:32:52,156
- He's right over there!
- Max!

461
00:32:52,239 --> 00:32:54,325
- Max!
- Oh, hello, Dr. Guggenheim.

462
00:32:54,408 --> 00:32:56,994
- What the hell do you think you're doing?
- We're having a fund-raiser for the...

463
00:32:57,077 --> 00:32:59,079
Turn that damn thing off!

464
00:32:59,830 --> 00:33:01,624
Tell me this isn't happening.

465
00:33:01,665 --> 00:33:04,752
Dr. Guggenheim, I'd rather not have
this conversation in front of my crew.

466
00:33:29,318 --> 00:33:30,986
...chapter seven.

467
00:33:31,904 --> 00:33:35,533
One more thing.
We have a new student with us today.

468
00:33:35,699 --> 00:33:39,036
His name's Max Fischer,
and he's actually asked...

469
00:33:39,161 --> 00:33:41,413
to say a few words to the class.

470
00:33:41,664 --> 00:33:44,333
Max, you want to take it away?

471
00:33:44,708 --> 00:33:47,128
Sure. Thanks very much.

472
00:33:48,754 --> 00:33:50,840
I just wanted to introduce myself.

473
00:33:56,679 --> 00:33:58,347
I'm Max Fischer.

474
00:33:58,389 --> 00:34:01,183
I'm a former student
of Rushmore Academy,

475
00:34:01,225 --> 00:34:03,936
which I recently
got expelled from.

476
00:34:06,147 --> 00:34:08,649
This is my first time
in a public school.

477
00:34:08,816 --> 00:34:12,111
I know you probably think I was born
with a silver spoon in my mouth,

478
00:34:12,194 --> 00:34:14,321
