01:19:56,230 --> 01:19:59,942
- You better believe it.
- Well, the plans were never
formally submitted to the city.

962
01:20:00,067 --> 01:20:02,319
- Were they supposed to be?
- I assume so.

963
01:20:02,445 --> 01:20:04,488
- Too late now.
<i>- Officers Brooks and Donovan...</i>

964
01:20:04,572 --> 01:20:06,991
<i>requesting additional units</i>
<i>at Grover Cleveland High School.</i>

965
01:20:07,074 --> 01:20:08,826
<i>- Units responding identify.</i>
- A program.

966
01:20:08,909 --> 01:20:12,746
Let me look at that.
Turn it, turn it.

967
01:20:12,830 --> 01:20:14,748
That's enough.

968
01:20:17,001 --> 01:20:19,753
- Excuse me. Right here.
- Thanks.

969
01:20:23,591 --> 01:20:25,634
Hi, Herman.

970
01:20:29,346 --> 01:20:31,932
Looks like Max
pulled a fast one on us.

971
01:20:39,857 --> 01:20:41,901
Thank you very much.

972
01:20:42,526 --> 01:20:46,572
I don't usually do this,
but this play means a lot to me,

973
01:20:46,655 --> 01:20:48,908
and I wanted
to make a dedication.

974
01:20:48,991 --> 01:20:52,661
So, I'll just say that this play
is dedicated to the memory of my mother,

975
01:20:52,703 --> 01:20:55,080
Eloise Fischer,

976
01:20:55,790 --> 01:20:58,959
and to Edward Appleby,
a friend of a friend.

977
01:21:00,044 --> 01:21:02,671
Also, you'll find a pair
of safety glasses and some earplugs...

978
01:21:02,713 --> 01:21:04,673
underneath your seats.

979
01:21:04,715 --> 01:21:08,344
Please feel free to use them.
Thank you very much.

980
01:21:15,017 --> 01:21:17,103
<i>Bravo Company, this is Tango 7.</i>
<i>Do you copy?</i>

981
01:21:17,186 --> 01:21:20,856
We order the military forces
of the United States to take action...

982
01:21:20,981 --> 01:21:23,484
This is a different kind of war.

983
01:21:23,567 --> 01:21:26,904
We are making progress,
progress, progress, progress.

984
01:21:38,082 --> 01:21:40,626
How long you been
in country, soldier?

985
01:21:40,751 --> 01:21:42,962
I ain't even here, Sergeant.

986
01:21:43,087 --> 01:21:45,047
I'm in Cheyenne, Wyoming.

987
01:21:46,340 --> 01:21:47,716
Right on, brother.

988
01:21:49,885 --> 01:21:52,012
Hoo. Hoo-hoo.

989
01:21:54,640 --> 01:21:57,643
Let's rock, Esposito!
I repeat, let's rock!

990
01:21:59,562 --> 01:22:01,397
Let's rock and roll!

991
01:22:35,389 --> 01:22:37,141
Fischer!

992
01:22:40,186 --> 01:22:41,937
I'm okay. Go, go, go, go.

993
01:22:42,605 --> 01:22:44,440
- Damn it!
- Take it easy, Dirk.

994
01:22:44,482 --> 01:22:46,609
- How much time do we got, Wood?
- Two minutes.

995
01:22:46,650 --> 01:22:49,195
- All right, bring me some more
ketchup very quickly, please.
- Effects!

996
01:22:49,278 --> 01:22:52,656
- This is gonna look stupid.
- No, it's not. It's gonna look real.

997
01:23:09,882 --> 01:23:13,093
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

998
01:23:13,552 --> 01:23:15,596
Hold this one too, okay?

999
01:23:19,016 --> 01:23:23,270
So, what do you think
of Max's latest opus?

1000
01:23:24,647 --> 01:23:26,565
It's good.

1001
01:23:29,151 --> 01:23:32,154
But let's hope
it's got a happy ending.

1002
01:23:49,755 --> 01:23:54,385
- Adios, Esposito.
- Adios, Sarge.

1003
01:23:54,552 --> 01:23:58,389
Say a prayer for Surf Boy,
wherever he is.

1004
01:23:58,472 --> 01:24:02,435
Semper fi, soldier.
Semper fi.

1005
01:24:02,560 --> 01:24:04,979
Sic transit gloria.

1006
01:24:05,271 --> 01:24:07,940
Maybe we'll meet again someday...

1007
01:24:08,107 --> 01:24:10,067
when the fighting stops.

1008
01:24:12,903 --> 01:24:15,906
Tag 'em and bag 'em, cherries!
We're movin' out!

1009
01:24:17,992 --> 01:24:19,728
I don't know but I've been told

1010
01:24:19,910 --> 01:24:22,204
I don't know but I've been told

1011
01:24:31,422 --> 01:24:33,340
Hello, Esposito.

1012
01:24:38,262 --> 01:24:40,097
Will you marry me, Le-Chahn?

1013
01:24:41,640 --> 01:24:43,434
You bet I will.

1014
01:24:57,281 --> 01:25:01,035
That's my son.
That's my Maxie.

1015
01:25:09,627 --> 01:25:12,505
I just didn't expect to see you here.

1016
01:25:12,755 --> 01:25:14,548
Did Max send you an invitation?

1017
01:25:14,632 --> 01:25:18,010
Yeah, and he told me to wear a tie.

1018
01:25:19,804 --> 01:25:24,058
- Congratulations, Max.
- Thank you very much, Mrs. Yang.

1019
01:25:24,183 --> 01:25:27,436
I, uh, actually wrote a different
version of the play two years ago,

1020
01:25:27,561 --> 01:25:29,355
but I couldn't
get it done over at Rushmore.

1021
01:25:29,480 --> 01:25:31,649
- Oh, really? Why?
- Too political?

1022
01:25:31,690 --> 01:25:34,652
No, a kid got his finger blown off
during rehearsals.

1023
01:25:34,735 --> 01:25:37,655
A very good evening
to you, Fischers. Hi.

1024
01:25:37,738 --> 01:25:40,199
Miss Cross, I'd like for you
to meet my father, Bert Fischer.

1025
01:25:40,282 --> 01:25:43,369
He's a barber.
This is my friend, Rosemary Cross.

1026
01:25:43,452 --> 01:25:46,622
- Hello, Rosemary.
- Nice to meet you at last, Bert.

1027
01:25:46,747 --> 01:25:48,207
Of course you know Mr. Blume.

1028
01:25:48,290 --> 01:25:52,586
I'd also like everyone to meet
Mr. and Mrs. Yang. This is Margaret.

1029
01:25:52,670 --> 01:25:55,422
- Hello, Margaret.
- It's nice to meet you, Miss Cross.

1030
01:25:55,506 --> 01:25:57,716
I'm surprised they let him build
a real campfire on the stage.

1031
01:25:57,800 --> 01:25:59,718
It's clearly a safety hazard.

1032
01:25:59,802 --> 01:26:03,222
- Well, last year,
he tried to raise piranhas.
- Yeah, I know he did.

1033
01:26:03,305 --> 01:26:06,475
- What did you think, Mr. Littlejeans?
- Best play ever, man.

1034
01:26:09,019 --> 01:26:10,980
I thought it was
a very realistic performance.

1035
01:26:11,021 --> 01:26:14,024
Yeah? Fischer stepped
over half my bloody lines.

1036
01:26:14,108 --> 01:26:16,068
That's funny.
I didn't notice.

1037
01:26:16,152 --> 01:26:18,696
Mr. Blume, how are Ronny and Donny
enjoying military school?

1038
01:26:18,779 --> 01:26:21,365
- They love it.
- Lucky bastards.

1039
01:26:22,074 --> 01:26:26,120
- I understand you're a neurosurgeon.
- No, I'm a barber.

1040
01:26:26,203 --> 01:26:28,998
But a lot of people make that mistake.

1041
01:26:34,044 --> 01:26:36,338
You were incredible tonight, Margaret.

1042
01:26:36,380 --> 01:26:39,592
- You were that poor girl.
- Thank you.

1043
01:26:39,675 --> 01:26:43,345
I loved it when you grabbed
onto the bottom of the chopper
as it was taking off.

1044
01:26:43,429 --> 01:26:45,389
- That was totally improvised.
- I know.

1045
01:26:45,431 --> 01:26:47,391
- Can I ask you a question?
- Of course.

1046
01:26:47,433 --> 01:26:49,935
Can you do
an Australian accent?

1047
01:26:50,019 --> 01:26:52,521
I'm working on something
that's set in the outback.

1048
01:26:52,605 --> 01:26:55,566
I really feel like celebrating,
you know?

1049
01:26:55,775 --> 01:26:59,487
- Would you care to dance?
- Oh, yes, I would love to.

1050
01:26:59,653 --> 01:27:01,155
- Great.
- Come on.

1051
01:27:01,697 --> 01:27:03,282
You're looking good, Bert.

1052
01:27:03,365 --> 01:27:05,326
Hello, Mr. Blume.

1053
01:27:05,743 --> 01:27:08,370
Hello, Margaret.
May I cut in?

1054
01:27:08,412 --> 01:27:11,415
I haven't had a chance to cut a rug
with your new girlfriend yet.

1055
01:27:11,457 --> 01:27:15,002
- Ah, new girlfriend.
- Yes, I am.

1056
01:27:15,085 --> 01:27:19,006
Find your own dance partner, Mr. Blume.
I'm spoken for.

1057
01:27:19,131 --> 01:27:22,927
No, it's okay.
He's my friend.

1058
01:27:28,599 --> 01:27:31,811
Well... you pulled it off.

1059
01:27:31,936 --> 01:27:35,231
Yeah, it went okay.
At least nobody got hurt.

1060
01:27:37,483 --> 01:27:38,943
Except you.

1061
01:27:40,903 --> 01:27:43,906
No, I didn't get hurt that bad.

1062
01:27:44,115 --> 01:27:47,159
Come on, you two. Shake a leg.

1063
01:27:49,495 --> 01:27:52,206
- Would you like to dance?
- Yeah, but...

1064
01:27:52,289 --> 01:27:56,043
Here, let's see if the deejay can play
something with a little more... Reuben!


